Am Freitag, den 10.04.2015, 14:23 +0200 schrieb Daniel B=C3=BCnzli:
> Le jeudi, 9 avril 2015 =C3=A0 14:24, Dario Teixeira a =C3=A9crit :
> > Below you'll find sample META files for each case.
>=20
> One thing this doesn't seem to answer is where the ppx binary is installe=
d. Doing a=20=20
>=20
> > find .opam/4.02.1/lib -name "META" | xargs cat | grep "^ *ppx"
>=20
> On my machine yields the following:=20=20
>=20=20=20
> ppx =3D "ppx_lwt"
> ppx =3D "./ppx_metaquot"
> ppx(-byte)=3D"./ppx_xtmpl"
>=20
> ppx(byte)=3D"./ppx_xtmpl.byte"
>=20
> which seems inconsistant with the semantics of fields in META files which=
 usually express their object w.r.t. to the package directory.=20=20

It is described in the man page for META. A command is not an object
file, and it would be inconsistent with the conceptual peculiarities if
we handled commands as objects.

Gerd
